# Financial Ratio Analysis

This notebook calculates key financial ratios commonly used in audit planning
to assess financial performance and identify potential audit risks.
import pandas as pd

income = pd.read_csv("../data/income_statement.csv")
balance = pd.read_csv("../data/balance_sheet.csv")
cashflow = pd.read_csv("../data/cash_flow_statement.csv")

financials = income.merge(balance, on="Year") \
                   .merge(cashflow, on="Year") \
                   .sort_values("Year") \
                   .reset_index(drop=True)

financials
financials["Gross_Margin"] = (financials["Revenue"] - financials["Cost"]) / financials["Revenue"]
financials[["Year", "Gross_Margin"]]
financials["Debt_Ratio"] = financials["Total_Liabilities"] / financials["Total_Assets"]
financials[["Year", "Debt_Ratio"]]
financials["AR_Turnover"] = financials["Revenue"] / financials["Accounts_Receivable"]
financials[["Year", "AR_Turnover"]]
financials["Inventory_Turnover"] = financials["Cost"] / financials["Inventory"]
financials[["Year", "Inventory_Turnover"]]
financials["OCF_to_NetProfit"] = financials["Operating_Cash_Flow"] / financials["Net_Profit"]
financials[["Year", "OCF_to_NetProfit"]]
## Audit Interpretation Summary

The calculated financial ratios provide insights into profitability,
liquidity, and operational efficiency. Certain trends and fluctuations
may indicate areas requiring further audit attention in subsequent analysis.
